31/10/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government plans to launch efforts to implement new EU-oriented reforms, according to a joint statement by Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul, Justice Minister Cemil Cicek and Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu on Friday (29 October). The new measures will be aimed at bringing the country's legislation in line with that of the EU, as well as address concerns raised in the European Commission's progress report on Turkey released earlier this month. (NTV - 29/10/04)
